<br>
Until this date, I cannot think of advanced weaponry that has been used by terrorists. Did we ever doubt terrorists would hesitate to use a nuclear device if they got their hands on it ? I wouldn't, still I feel more unsafe now.<br>
<br>
Of course, the fact that terrorists didn't have access to WMD's in the past, does not mean they will never get it. The risk is there, but I don't see it as inevitable. How much the risk really is, I cannot say. Who knows ya'll are right and Saddam already supplied terrorists with chemical weapons. It would be a bad situation. What about Russia's cache of nuclear devices ? How careful is Russia with their sample of smallpox ? What if some Eurotrash pisses off Rathic and he uses a loophole in the security system to bomb Paris <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ?<br>
<br>
Maybe we're more scared because 9-11 seemed like a movie. If something like that could happen, why not some of the more horrific scenarios that Hollywood has presented.<br>
<br>
Well, I'm rambling and going nowhere with this. My point, 9-11 was a wakeup-call, but I am still fairly confident we have the ability to prevent the really big disasters from happening. On terrorism itself, I don't think we could totally stop it, except by removing their ideas. I believe extremism can die out eventually, at least to the point it will become fairly insignificant. <p>---------------<br>
